# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  BEACON — Environment Template
#  Copy this file to `.env` (or `.env.local`) and fill in values as needed.
#
#  IMPORTANT — read before filling anything in:
#  BEACON works fully WITHOUT any third-party API keys. Aviation, maritime,
#  satellites, fires, earthquakes, weather, news, CVEs, etc. all use public
#  keyless feeds (OpenSky/adsb.lol, Celestrak, NASA FIRMS CSV, USGS, NOAA, …).
#
#  As of this revision the application code reads:
#  - SCANNER_URL / SCANNER_KEY  → RECON toolkit (separate backend)
#  - GROQ_API_KEY / OPENROUTER_API_KEY  → AI intelligence briefs
#  - OPENMHZ_SYSTEM  → Local P25/RF radio feeds (e.g. mcsdr)
#  - BEACON_REDIS_URL  → Redis for caching, feed state, health checks
#
#  All other keys below are OPTIONAL and reserved for higher rate limits /
#  future data sources — set them only if you extend the code or hit rate
#  limits on the public feeds.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  RECON SCANNER BACKEND  ── powers the RECON toolkit (Nmap, DNS, WHOIS,
#  SSL, subdomains, tech fingerprint, geoloc, vuln scans). Requires the
#  separate Beacon scanner backend. SCANNER_KEY MUST equal backend BEACON_KEY.
#  Generate one with:  openssl rand -hex 32
#  Leave both empty to disable RECON features (UI returns 503).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SCANNER_URL=
SCANNER_KEY=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  AI INTELLIGENCE LAYER  ── enables AI-driven situational briefs
#  Get free keys at https://console.groq.com/keys or https://openrouter.ai/keys
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GROQ_API_KEY=
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  REDIS  ── enables caching, feed state persistence, health checks
#  Use a local Redis, Upstash, or any Redis-compatible endpoint.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BEACON_REDIS_URL=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  RF / P25 RADIO FEEDS  ── local OpenMHz-compatible P25 system
#  Set OPENMHZ_SYSTEM to the system ID (e.g. 'mcsdr' for Monroe County MCSDR)
#  Optional: OPENMHZ_API_KEY if your local endpoint requires auth
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
OPENMHZ_SYSTEM=
OPENMHZ_API_KEY=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  AUTH  ── enables multi-user, persistent prefs, API key management
#  Generate AUTH_SECRET with: openssl rand -base64 32
#  Configure OAuth providers (Google, GitHub) in their respective consoles.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
AUTH_SECRET=
AUTH_GOOGLE_ID=
AUTH_GOOGLE_SECRET=
AUTH_GITHUB_ID=
AUTH_GITHUB_SECRET=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  OPTIONAL DATA-SOURCE KEYS  (not read by current code — future / upgrades)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# NASA FIRMS — active wildfire hotspots.
# Free, instant. Enter an email at the page below and the MAP_KEY is emailed
# to you (looks like 'abcdef1234567890abcdef1234567890'). Limit: 5000 req /
# 10 min. The app already uses the keyless FIRMS CSV; a key only matters if
# you switch to the per-area FIRMS API.
#   Get it: https://firms.modaps.eosdis.nasa.gov/api/map_key/
FIRMS_API_KEY=

# OpenSky Network — aviation (higher rate limits than the keyless feed).
# Free account. Since March 2025 OpenSky uses OAuth2 (username/password auth
# is dropped). Create an account, open the Account page, create a new API
# client, and copy the client_id / client_secret.
#   Get it: https://opensky-network.org/  (Account → API client)
OPENSKY_CLIENT_ID=
OPENSKY_CLIENT_SECRET=

# N2YO — satellite tracking / pass predictions.
# Free. Register, then Profile page → scroll down → "generate API key".
# The key cannot be changed once issued. Limit: 1000 req / hour.
#   Get it: https://www.n2yo.com/login/register/  (then Profile)
N2YO_API_KEY=

# aisstream.io — live maritime AIS vessel positions via WebSocket.
# Free. Register, then create a key on the API Keys page. Used in the
# subscription message to wss://stream.aisstream.io/v0/stream.
#   Get it: https://aisstream.io/  (sign up → API Keys)
AIS_API_KEY=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  TELEGRAM OSINT  ── public channels to scrape for geoparsed intel
#  Comma-separated usernames (no @). Channels must have web preview enabled.
#  Default if unset: osintdefender,insiderpaper,aljazeeraenglish,nexta_live,war_monitor
# OSIRIS_TELEGRAM_CHANNELS=
BEACON_TELEGRAM_CHANNELS=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  RUNTIME
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Host port the web UI is published on (container always listens on 3000).
# Change this if 3000 is already taken on your host.
BEACON_PORT=3000

# Set by the Docker image already — override only if needed.
# NODE_ENV=production
# PORT=3000
# HOSTNAME=0.0.0.0